00:53:11,146 --> 00:53:13,981
After Shrike drowned,
they never found the body.

1018
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:16,316
What are you suggesting?

1019
00:53:19,487 --> 00:53:21,488
Arthur Tressler presents

1020
00:53:21,740 --> 00:53:22,990
Jack Wilder,

1021
00:53:23,241 --> 00:53:24,283
Henley Reeves,

1022
00:53:24,492 --> 00:53:25,826
Merritt McKinney,

1023
00:53:25,994 --> 00:53:27,578
and Daniel Atlas.

1024
00:53:27,787 --> 00:53:29,496
The Four Horsemen.

1025
00:53:34,669 --> 00:53:36,295
Thank you. Before we begin,

1026
00:53:36,379 --> 00:53:38,422
we'd like to single out
two people in particular.

1027
00:53:38,506 --> 00:53:40,966
A man and a woman to whom
we'd like to dedicate tonight's performance.

1028
00:53:41,050 --> 00:53:42,760
FBI Agent Dylan Rhodes

1029
00:53:42,844 --> 00:53:48,557
and the lovely, if somewhat inexperienced,
Interpol Agent Alma Dray, everyone.

1030
00:53:50,018 --> 00:53:53,771
Yeah, Agent Rhodes
has personally vowed to nail us.

1031
00:53:53,855 --> 00:53:58,358
And we encourage him to do so
if he has the brains and the fur.

1032
00:54:02,530 --> 00:54:04,323
What is magic?

1033
00:54:04,532 --> 00:54:07,201
Our argument,
nothing but targeted deception.

1034
00:54:08,912 --> 00:54:10,537
So I want you to look.

1035
00:54:10,872 --> 00:54:12,915
Look as closely as possible.

1036
00:54:13,333 --> 00:54:17,294
Because the tricks you are about to see
may not seem connected.

1037
00:54:17,378 --> 00:54:19,296
But we assure you, they are.

1038
00:54:20,256 --> 00:54:23,050
Is what follows 100 different tricks?

1039
00:54:23,384 --> 00:54:27,054
Or is it one giant illusion?

1040
00:54:34,729 --> 00:54:37,898
And now for one
of the oldest tricks in the book.

1041
00:54:37,982 --> 00:54:39,942
Danny, if you wouldn't mind
opening up the box,

1042
00:54:40,026 --> 00:54:42,152
and showing everybody
that it's completely empty.

1043
00:54:42,487 --> 00:54:46,490
Now, we're gonna need
12 courageous volunteers.

1044
00:54:46,699 --> 00:54:48,826
I'm gonna take sweet little Fluffy here,

1045
00:54:49,035 --> 00:54:51,703
and put her inside this mystery box.

1046
00:54:52,288 --> 00:54:55,207
There are two pencils out there.
Hold 'em up high. Let me see 'em.

1047
00:54:55,291 --> 00:54:56,667
- Here!
- Yeah!

1048
00:54:57,335 --> 00:54:59,169
And now, you will say the magic word.

1049
00:54:59,379 --> 00:55:00,504
Abracadabra.

1050
00:55:00,588 --> 00:55:03,632
Yes, and I will wave this magic wand
for no reason. And then...

1051
00:55:03,716 --> 00:55:06,176
Fluffy has magically vanished
before your very eyes.

1052
00:55:07,720 --> 00:55:11,181
If you haven't experienced mass hypnosis,
you're about to.

1053
00:55:11,432 --> 00:55:12,432
And sleep.

1054
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:15,352
Down, down. Sleep, sleep. Completely sleep.

1055
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:17,020
Good, good. Sleep, sleep.

1056
00:55:17,230 --> 00:55:21,316
And now we are gonna debunk
a few magic myths this evening.

1057
00:55:21,526 --> 00:55:24,444
We all know that Fluffy is,
in fact, alive and well.

1058
00:55:24,988 --> 00:55:27,406
And Fluffy has miraculously appeared.

1059
00:55:27,615 --> 00:55:28,991
As has the mirror

1060
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:31,535
which makes the box only
appear as though it's empty.

1061
00:55:31,744 --> 00:55:33,787
When you hear the word freeze

1062
00:55:33,997 --> 00:55:35,581
you are all football players.

1063
00:55:36,749 --> 00:55:39,209
And your job is to tackle,

1064
00:55:39,419 --> 00:55:40,711
dismantle,

1065
00:55:40,920 --> 00:55:42,087
crush,

1066
00:55:42,297 --> 00:55:44,631
tear limb from limb,

1067
00:55:45,008 --> 00:55:46,758
the quarterback.

1068
00:55:48,136 --> 00:55:51,597
Now, we've all heard
of pulling the rabbit out of the hat.

1069
00:55:51,681 --> 00:55:54,683
But has anyone heard
of pulling a hat out of a rabbit?

1070
00:55:59,147 --> 00:56:01,481
You will know who the quarterback is.

1071
00:56:01,649 --> 00:56:05,110
He will be the one saying that word.

1072
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:06,320
Freeze.

1073
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:18,957
Three, two, one...

1074
00:56:19,834 --> 00:56:22,169
- Elvis, help me out, bud.
- Thank you very much.

1075
00:56:22,378 --> 00:56:24,796
In Jack's bowl
are ping pong balls with section numbers.

1076
00:56:25,006 --> 00:56:27,007
Jack, could you hand me a section number?

1077
00:56:27,216 --> 00:56:28,592
Thank you. We are looking at Section B.

1078
00:56:28,801 --> 00:56:30,552
Where is Section B?

1079
00:56:30,637 --> 00:56:33,096
Okay. There.
It's gonna be one of you guys. Get ready.

1080
00:56:33,598 --> 00:56:34,931
I don't know why everybody's happy.

1081
00:56:35,016 --> 00:56:36,058
It's only them.

1082
00:56:36,351 --> 00:56:37,684
Merritt, can I get a row, please?

1083
00:56:45,401 --> 00:56:47,277
Put your hands in the middle.
One, two, three...

1084
00:56:47,362 --> 00:56:48,654
Kill the quarterback!

1085
00:56:48,946 --> 00:56:50,572
Get on back to your seats.

1086
00:56:50,782 --> 00:56:52,783
I got a feeling I'm gonna be seeing you soon.

1087
00:57:25,358 --> 00:57:26,775
I guess you have lost some weight.

1088
00:57:42,417 --> 00:57:43,834
At the intermission,

1089
00:57:43,918 --> 00:57:46,253
we asked you to write down
your current bank balance,

1090
00:57:46,337 --> 00:57:47,838
and seal it in an envelope.

1091
00:57:47,922 --> 00:57:50,382
Now it's time to take those envelopes out.
Everyone take 'em out.

1092
00:57:52,176 --> 00:57:56,722
Now, everybody, shout out your name.
All at once. Go.

1093
00:57:58,433 --> 00:57:59,474
Shout 'em out.

1094
00:58:02,061 --> 00:58:03,979
Clement? Frannick?

1095
00:58:04,188 --> 00:58:06,106
- Yeah! Up here!
- Way up there.

1096
00:58:06,315 --> 00:58:08,275
Okay. Dina? Robertson?

1097
00:58:08,484 --> 00:58:09,609
That's me!

1098
00:58:09,944 --> 00:58:12,279
Okay. Names. Names. Let's go.

1099
00:58:13,656 --> 00:58:15,615
Josepha Hickey?

1100
00:58:15,700 --> 00:58:16,742
That's me!

1101
00:58:16,826 --> 00:58:19,745
Josepha, I want you to focus on your balance,

1102
00:58:19,954 --> 00:58:21,913
and count from one to ten out loud.

1103
00:58:22,123 --> 00:58:23,790
One, two, three, four, five...

1104
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:25,125
Stop.

1105
00:58:25,251 --> 00:58:26,460
Is the first digit 5?

1106
00:58:27,086 --> 00:58:28,044
Yes.

1107
00:58:28,129 --> 00:58:29,421
Do it again. This time, faster.

1108
00:58:29,547 --> 00:58:30,964
One, two, three, four, five, six...

1109
00:58:31,048 --> 00:58:32,132
Stop.

1110
00:58:32,842 --> 00:58:34,342
Six. Again.

1111
00:58:34,427 --> 00:58:35,427
One, two...

1112
00:58:35,511 --> 00:58:39,473
Josepha, is your
bank balance $562 as of today?

1113
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:41,975
Yeah. That's what I got.

1114
00:58:43,728 --> 00:58:45,270
Unfortunately, you're wrong.

1115
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:46,521
Okay, Dina,

1116
00:58:48,399 --> 00:58:49,441
1,

1117
00:58:50,026 --> 00:58:51,067
4,

1118
00:58:51,778 --> 00:58:52,778
7,

1119
00:58:53,738 --> 00:58:55,197
- 7.
- Yeah.

1120
00:58:55,281 --> 00:58:59,075
You think it is.
But in fact, you too are wrong.

1121
00:58:59,285 --> 00:59:00,327
Clement...

1122
00:59:00,536 --> 00:59:03,497
You do not have $6,500 in your account.

1123
00:59:03,706 --> 00:59:07,501
In fact, everybody stand up. Everybody.

1124
00:59:09,504 --> 00:59:12,172
Yeah. Put your envelopes to your forehead.

1125
00:59:13,800 --> 00:59:15,258
Focus on your number.

1126
00:59:19,514 --> 00:59:22,599
This is... Oh, dear. Just as I feared.

1127
00:59:22,725 --> 00:59:24,893
Oh, this is strange.

1128
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:28,480
You know, I hate to say this,
but you're all wrong.

1129
00:59:28,689 --> 00:59:30,524
Every last one of you is dead wrong

1130
00:59:30,608 --> 00:59:32,567
about what you think is in your account.

1131
00:59:32,819 --> 00:59:34,569
Okay, you can sit down now.

1132
00:59:34,946 --> 00:59:37,113
Oh, yeah. I almost forgot.

1133
00:59:37,198 --> 00:59:40,158
This evening would not be possible

1134
00:59:40,243 --> 00:59:44,329
if it weren't for our great benefactor
Arthur Tressler.

1135
00:59:45,289 --> 00:59:46,915
Big applause! Big applause!

1136
00:59:47,124 --> 00:59:49,584
Art, actually, why don't you come up on stage
for the finale?

1137
00:59:49,794 --> 00:59:51,461
- Come on down, Art!
- Come on down, Art!

1138
00:59:51,671 --> 00:59:53,463
There he goes. Okay, good.

1139
00:59:53,673 --> 00:59:54,714
Are we on red?

1140
00:59:54,799 --> 00:59:56,716
Bright red. We're all standing by.

1141
00:59:56,926 --> 00:59:58,385
All right, no one leaves the theater.
No one.

1142
00:59:58,469 --> 00:59:59,511
There he goes.

1143
01:00:00,263 --> 01:00:02,347
Now, Art, did you fill out your envelope?

1144
01:00:02,557 --> 01:00:04,391
Well, no need. We've done it for you.

1145
01:00:05,059 --> 01:00:10,146
Now, Art, I took a guess.
North of 140. Am I right?

1146
01:00:11,274 --> 01:00:13,942
That's 140 million, by the way.

1147
01:00:17,572 --> 01:00:18,572
I'm sorry, Merritt.

1148
01:00:18,739 --> 01:00:21,741
How can he be right about his balance
and everyone else be wrong?

1149
01:00:21,826 --> 01:00:25,203
I think possibly because he too is wrong.

1150
01:00:25,580 --> 01:00:27,789
Everybody, take out your paper.

1151
01:00:27,874 --> 01:00:32,419
And using the flashlight under your seat,
start to warm up that paper.

1152
01:00:32,587 --> 01:00:35,755
I think your correct balance begins to appear.

1153
01:00:39,468 --> 01:00:42,721
Now, Art, don't worry,
we have a flashlight for you.

1154
01:00:42,930 --> 01:00:43,972
Yes.

1155
01:00:50,730 --> 01:00:52,647
Look.

1156
01:00:52,940 --> 01:00:54,149
What's going on there, Daniel?

1157
01:00:54,358 --> 01:00:59,779
Wait. This is weird.
A second ago, it said $144,579,651.

1158
01:00:59,864 --> 01:01:00,864
But now...

1159
01:01:01,490 --> 01:01:04,492
Now it says $70,000 less.

1160
01:01:07,872 --> 01:01:10,206
- Josepha, can you stand up?
- Yes.

1161
01:01:10,291 --> 01:01:11,917
Now, what is your new number?

1162
01:01:12,627 --> 01:01:16,963
$70,562 now in my account.

1163
01:01:20,259 --> 01:01:25,805
Is it possible that Josepha's balance went up
the exact amount that Art's went down?

1164
01:01:26,140 --> 01:01:28,642
Hey. Check it out. It's happening again.

1165
01:01:28,809 --> 01:01:29,851
Is it?

1166
01:01:31,145 --> 01:01:33,480
It is.

1167
01:01:33,814 --> 01:01:36,983
Art's balance has gone down another 280K.

1168
01:01:37,151 --> 01:01:39,194
Dina Robertson? What did yours say?

1169
01:01:39,445 --> 01:01:43,198
$281,477.

1170
01:01:47,161 --> 01:01:48,828
We have a confession to make.

1171
01:01:49,038 --> 01:01:51,039
She's right. We lied about something.

1172
01:01:51,123 --> 01:01:52,791
Yes. None of you were chosen at random.

1173
01:01:52,917 --> 01:01:55,335
All of you have one thing in common.

1174
01:01:55,878 --> 01:01:57,796
Everyone in this room was a victim

1175
01:01:57,880 --> 01:02:00,674
of the hard times that hit one of
America's most treasured cities.

1176
01:02:00,758 --> 01:02:03,343
Some of you lost your houses, your cars.

1177
01:02:03,844 --> 01:02:05,887
- Your businesses.
- Your loved ones.

1178
01:02:06,013 --> 01:02:09,182
But all of you were insured
by the same company.

1179
01:02:09,350 --> 01:02:10,976
Tressler Insurance.

1180
01:02:12,520 --> 01:02:13,520
You were abandoned.

1181
01:02:13,604 --> 01:02:14,688
You were loopholed...

1182
01:02:14,772 --> 01:02:15,981
out of your settlements.

1183
01:02:17,358 --> 01:02:19,985
This is all for show. Correct?

1184
01:02:20,194 --> 01:02:21,444
All meaning we're doing it onstage

1185
01:02:21,529 --> 01:02:22,737
in front of a paying audience?

1186
01:02:22,905 --> 01:02:24,531
Then, yes, it's for show.

1187
01:02:24,824 --> 01:02:27,325
I've got $82,000 in my bank account!

1188
01:02:27,493 --> 01:02:29,327
It says it right here on my cell phone!

1189
01:02:29,578 --> 01:02:32,539
Everybody, look at your cell phones
right now! Everybody!

1190
01:02:40,506 --> 01:02:41,506
Is this for real?

1191
01:02:41,716 --> 01:02:42,882
I don't know.

1192
01:02:43,175 --> 01:02:44,259
Is this happening?

1193
01:02:44,427 --> 01:02:46,011
I don't know! I can't tell!

1194
01:02:46,762 --> 01:02:48,888
Hey! Did you do this?

1195
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:51,349
How could we, Art?

1196
01:02:51,559 --> 01:02:52,726
We don't have your password.

1197
01:02:52,893 --> 01:02:56,187
We'd need access to information
we could never get our hands on.

1198
01:02:56,397 --> 01:03:00,108
Ah, yes, security questions, for instance, like,
I don't know, your mother's maiden name

1199
01:03:00,234 --> 01:03:01,776
or the name of your first pet.

1200
01:03:01,902 --> 01:03:03,695
Where would we get that information, Art?

1201
01:03:04,071 --> 01:03:05,697
You certainly would never tell us.

1202
01:03:08,492 --> 01:03:10,702
We got confirmation.
It's really happening. They robbed him.

1203
01:03:12,913 --> 01:03:14,372
Do not let them get away.

1204
01:03:14,457 --> 01:03:16,458
Hey, we left you the jet and the Rolls.

1205
01:03:23,424 --> 01:03:24,758
You got hell to pay!

1206
01:03:27,762 --> 01:03:28,762
Stop!

1207
01:03:29,472 --> 01:03:31,264
Stop! Nobody move!

1208
01:03:33,225 --> 01:03:34,309
Freeze!

1209
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:36,102
Quarterback!

1210
01:03:38,981 --> 01:03:41,399
We are The Four Horsemen.

1211
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:42,525
Good night.

1212
01:03:54,789 --> 01:03:56,164
Get 'em off me!

1213
01:03:56,916 --> 01:03:58,500
Get off! Get off me!

1214
01:04:08,886 --> 01:04:10,303
Get off me!

1215
01:04:18,604 --> 01:04:20,772
All right. I want everyone
on the street! Everyone!

1216
01:04:27,696 --> 01:04:29,531
Quarterback!

1217
01:04:31,075 --> 01:04:33,827
Fuller, meet me in front of the theater
and bring the tracker.

1218
01:04:34,370 --> 01:04:36,663
Let's go! Let's go! Now! Come on! Let's go!

1219
01:04:36,831 --> 01:04:37,914
Give me the tracker.

1220
01:04:38,374 --> 01:04:39,374
Let's go.

1221
01:04:43,587 --> 01:04:44,712
FBI! Clear!

1222
01:04:45,422 --> 01:04:46,422
- Dylan!
- Damn.

1223
01:04:46,715 --> 01:04:47,674
What have you got?

1224
01:04:47,758 --> 01:04:49,342
That's him right there. Follow the red dot.

1225
01:04:49,426 --> 01:04:52,470
All right, I'll take this.
Go. Box 'em. Cut 'em off that way.

1226
01:04:54,390 --> 01:04:55,890
He's turning left on Burgundy.

1227
01:05:32,970 --> 01:05:34,262
Hey! Move!

1228
01:05:34,597 --> 01:05:35,930
Move! Move!

1229
01:05:38,559 --> 01:05:40,101
I got him heading north on Bourbon.

1230
01:05:40,477 --> 01:05:42,187
- Sorry. Move, move!
- Hey!

1231
01:05:42,271 --> 01:05:44,063
Hey, excuse me. Move, move! Excuse me.

1232
01:05:55,534 --> 01:05:57,202
I've lost him at Bourbon.

1233
01:06:02,583 --> 01:06:03,958
Damn! Where are you?

1234
01:06:16,472 --> 01:06:17,680
Excuse me.

1235
01:06:23,979 --> 01:06:25,605
He's heading south on Exchange Place.

1236
01:06:28,150 --> 01:06:29,192
Stop!

1237
01:06:36,200 --> 01:06:37,408
What are you doing?

1238
01:06:40,996 --> 01:06:42,413
He's going in Napoleon House.

1239
01:06:45,250 --> 01:06:47,210
Move! Move!

1240
01:06:47,670 --> 01:06:49,212
Move out of the way!

1241
01:06:49,880 --> 01:06:50,880
Hey!

1242
01:06:51,715 --> 01:06:52,715
Move!

1243
01:06:55,010 --> 01:06:57,261
He's in the bathroom.
I have him in the bathroom.

1244
01:06:57,388 --> 01:06:59,681
No! No! No!

1245
01:07:01,558 --> 01:07:02,725
Freeze!

1246
01:07:03,560 --> 01:07:05,019
Lower your weapons!

1247
01:07:05,104 --> 01:07:08,439
What? I'm tracking myself!

1248
01:07:08,941 --> 01:07:10,900
The Horsemen left egg on the face
of what they call

1249
01:07:10,985 --> 01:07:16,280
the alphabet agencies, calling into question
the efficacy of the FBI's task force

1250
01:07:16,532 --> 01:07:19,033
as well as the man in charge
of the investigation,

1251
01:07:19,118 --> 01:07:22,620
Special Agent Dylan Rhodes,
who was publicly ridiculed,

1252
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:25,581
and even tackled at tonight's performance.

1253
01:07:25,916 --> 01:07:27,208
Talk about a fumble.

1254
01:07:27,418 --> 01:07:29,252
This is quickly becoming a national story,

1255
01:07:29,336 --> 01:07:32,130
as The Horsemen have now seemingly
pulled off the impossible

1256
01:07:32,214 --> 01:07:34,507
for the second time in as many days.

1257
01:07:34,925 --> 01:07:38,094
Two nights ago in Vegas, The Horsemen
seemingly robbed a bank in Paris...

1258
01:07:38,262 --> 01:07:39,429
Hey.

1259
01:07:40,723 --> 01:07:43,266
- What are you doing?
- I'm having a drink.

1260
01:07:46,437 --> 01:07:47,770
I came to get you.

1261
01:07:48,230 --> 01:07:49,230
I'm worried about you.

1262
01:07:49,314 --> 01:07:51,149
You're worried about me.
Well, I'm worried about you.

1263
